oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Men working on train cars
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of four men working on train cars to move rocks and dirt. A crane (on left) hoists a large rock suspended by cables and chains. It is possible this photo was taken at a phosphate plant.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Men; Laborers; Railroad cars; Rocks
